org.mobicents.slee.enabler.sip
Class SubscriptionData

java.lang.Object
  org.mobicents.slee.enabler.sip.SubscriptionData
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Externalizable, java.io.Serializable
public class SubscriptionData
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Externalizable

Static information needed to create a SIP subscription. Example of usage: SubscriptionData subscriptionData = new SubscriptionData().setSubscriberURI(subscriber ).setNotifierURI(notifier).setEventPackage (EVENT_PACKAGE).setExpires(expires). setAcceptedContentTypes(ACCEPTED_CONTENT_TYPES ).setEventParameters(EVENT_PARAMETERS);

Author:
martins

isSupportResourceLists

public boolean isSupportResourceLists()
Indicates if the subscription should support resource lists as the notifier. If true the enabler includes all the mandatory accepted content types (rlmi and multipart) related with RLS notifications, it also includes the mandatory Supported header.

Returns:
